title: Static Analysis

android.permission.INTERNET.description: Allows an application to create network sockets.

android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the status of all networks.

android.permission.WAKE_LOCK.description: Allows an application to prevent the phone from going to sleep.

android.permission.RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETE.description: Allows an application to start itself as soon as the system has finished booting. This can make it take longer to start the phone and allow the application to slow down the overall phone by always running.

android.permission.VIBRATE.description: Allows the application to control the vibrator.

android.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION.description: Access fine location sources, such as the Global Positioning System on the phone, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine where you are and may consume additional battery power.

com.lumoslabs.lumosity.permission.C2D_ME.description: Allows the application to receive push notifications.

com.google.android.c2dm.permission.RECEI.description: Permission for cloud to device messaging.

"fit_test_edu_memory_matrix_description" : "Memory Matrix challenges you to use your visuospatial sketchpad — a concept from psychologist Alan Baddeley's model for working memory. 

Associated with several parts of your brain, this important cognitive tool stores visual information, like color or shape, and spatial information, like location."

"fit_test_edu_speed_match_description" : "Speed Match challenges a type of information processing called visual processing. Your brain must process the symbols on the flashcards to make a quick decision. 

This seemingly simple process involves many parts of your brain, such as your visual cortex. These neurons, located at the back of your brain, process shape, color, and movement — turning raw stimuli into useful information."
"fit_test_edu_speed_match_title" : "This game challenged your information processing skills."

"fit_test_edu_train_of_thought_description" : "Attention is a limited resource that can track only so much information at once. The more trains you focus on, the harder it becomes to guide a single train correctly. 

To do well at this game, you must constantly balance two processes: focusing on necessary information while ignoring the unnecessary."
"fit_test_edu_train_of_thought_title" : "Train of Thought challenged your divided attention."
"fit_test_error_loading_results" : "We're having trouble connecting right now. Keep going and we'll send your results at the end of your Fit Test."

"fit_test_report_training_program" : "Ready for your training program? You'll get a new workout every day."
"fittest_complete_workout" : "Complete your Fit Test to unlock today’s free games."

"fittest_edu_chalkboardchallenge_description" : "Chalkboard Challenge requires more than just fast mental arithmetic.

Answering quickly requires you to use your number sense, which allows you to compare two expressions using estimation — without doing all the calculations in your head."

"fittest_edu_ebbandflow_description" : "Ebb and Flow exercises your ability to switch between two competing ways we process direction: motion, and pointing.

The ability to quickly ignore a goal to take on a different one is a key element to your cognitive flexibility."
"fittest_edu_ebbandflow_title" : "Ebb and Flow challenged your task switching"

"insight_3_calculation_popup_body" : "Your strengths and weaknesses are based on the Lumosity Performance Index (LPI) for each game. LPI is a standardized scale that allows comparisons across games with different scoring methods.

These results are based on your current game LPI, which is updated each time you play the game. Only games played in the last six months are included."

"insight_4_calculation_popup_body" : "Your results are based on changes in the Lumosity Performance Index (LPI) for each game. LPI is a standardized scale that allows comparisons across games with different scoring methods.

For each game, your most recent game LPI was compared to your game LPI from 30 days ago. Only games played at least once in the last month are included."
"insights_dialog_speed_accuracy_nodata_body" : "We're still creating your report. Come back tomorrow!"

"insights_dialog_unlock_body" : "Every game you play in your workouts or from the Games page counts toward unlocking your Insights.

For higher quality insights, aim for a wide variety of games."

"insights_ebbflow_info_text" : "First, we compiled the Lumosity community's Ebb and Flow gameplays and grouped them by score. Then we calculated the average speed and accuracy for each “score group.” Based on your last Ebb and Flow score, we compare your speed and accuracy to that of your group.

If your speed percentile is higher than your accuracy percentile, your marker will be closer to the “Speed” side of the scale. If your accuracy percentile is higher, your marker will tend towards “Accuracy.”"

"insights_ebbflow_science" : "When you take on a task that challenges you to be fast and accurate, you face a “speed-accuracy tradeoff.” If you go as fast as possible, you tend to sacrifice accuracy, and vice versa. But which one is more important? It depends on the person and the task.

For this Insight, we compare your Ebb and Flow gameplays to millions of others and analyze how you balance speed and accuracy when you play. Next time, see if you can switch between the two. Find the balance that works best for you!"

"insights_lim_info_text" : "Each time you respond correctly, we measure the time you take to respond. We then calculate two median response times: one for matching flocks, another for non-matching flocks. We use these medians to determine your speed, expressed as the number of correct responses per minute."

"lim_compare_1" : "You are more sensitive to non-matching flocks than others your age."
"lim_compare_2" : "You are just as sensitive to non-matching flocks as other people your age."
"lim_compare_3" : "You are less sensitive to non-matching flocks than other people your age."

"lim_compare_adaptive" : "Compared to others your age, you are adaptive. Adaptive players slow down more for non-matching flocks because they adjust their speed for accuracy. When you play, remember also to keep up the pace so you can score higher."

"lim_compare_balanced" : "Compared to others your age, you are balanced. Balanced players slow down just a little for non-matching flocks — taking more time for accuracy while keeping a brisk pace. As you play, you could try either by pushing your speed or focusing more on precision."

"lim_compare_consistent" : "Compared to others your age, you are consistent. Consistent players don’t slow down for non-matching flocks. They maintain a steady pace, even at the risk of a few mistakes, and respond to more flocks overall. As you play, remember to stay accurate as you race through flocks."
"lim_compare_footer" : "Also, play styles can vary over time. Come back to see if your style changes!"

"lim_report_description" : "In Lost in Migration, people often respond more slowly to non-matching flocks — when the birds face different directions.

That's because the brain's selective attention must simultaneously target the middle bird and filter out the flock."
"lim_user_2" : "You respond only %1$d%% slower to non-matching flocks. Nice!"
"lim_user_3" : "Wow! You respond just %1$d%% slower to non-matching flocks."
"lim_user_4" : "You respond just as quickly to non-matching flocks. Awesome!"
"lim_user_5" : "Incredible — you respond faster to non-matching flocks!"
"lim_user_encouragement_1" : "The shorter this gap, the faster you filter out the rest of the flock."
"lim_user_encouragement_2" : "You're doing a great job at filtering out the rest of the flock."
"lim_user_encouragement_3" : "These results are extraordinary. Most people slow down for non-matching flocks!"

"fit_test_edu_speed_match_description" : "図形スピードマッチは視覚情報処理と呼ばれる情報処理能力のトレーニングです。表示されるシンボルを処理していくのに素早く決断をしなければなりません。


単純な処理のように見えますが、視覚野など脳の多くの部分を使います。これらのニューロンは脳の後部にあり、形・色や動きを処理し、受け取った刺激を有益な情報に変換します。"
"fit_test_edu_speed_match_title" : "このゲームは情報処理能力のトレーニングです。"

"fit_test_edu_train_of_thought_description" : "一度に払える注意力は限られていて、処理できる情報にも限度があります。例えば、多くの汽車に注意を払うほど、一つの汽車を正しい駅に導くのが難しくなります。

このゲームでは、重要な情報に注意を払いながら、必要でない情報を無視するという二つの処理の均衡を常に保つ必要があります。"
"fit_test_edu_train_of_thought_title" : "機関車ラッシュは分割的注意力のトレーニングです。"

"insight_3_calculation_popup_body" : "あなたの強みと弱点は、それぞれのゲームの Lumosity パフォーマンス指数 (LPI) を基にして計算されています。LPI はトレーニングスコアから算出した標準尺度で、異なるスコアの手段をもつ複数のゲーム結果を比較するのに役立ちます。

これらの結果はあなたの現在のゲーム LPI に基づきます。ゲーム LPI はそのゲームをプレイするごとに更新され、過去６ヶ月にプレイしたゲームのみが対象となります。"

"insight_4_calculation_popup_body" : "あなたの強みと弱点は、それぞれのゲームの Lumosity パフォーマンス指数 (LPI) を基にして計算されています。LPI はトレーニングスコアから算出した標準尺度で、異なるスコアの手段をもつ複数のゲーム結果を比較するのに役立ちます。

"insights_ebbflow_info_text" : "「落ち葉フロー」のゲームプレイを近似したスコアのグループに分け、それぞれのグループの速度と正確さを分析しました。あなたの最新の「落ち葉フロー」のスコアから、あなたの速度と正確さをあなたのグループ内で比較します。

あなたの速度のパーセンタイルが精度パーセンタイルより高い場合、あなたのスライダーは「スピード」に近くなります。あなたの精度パーセンタイルが高い場合、あなたのスライダーは「正確さ」に近くなります。"

"insights_ebbflow_science" : "速度と正確さが要求されるタスクには、「速度・精度のトレードオフ」という問題があります。速くプレイしようとすると、正確さを欠くことがあり、逆に正確さを求めた場合速度が落ちることがあります。速度と正確さのどちらを選べばいいのでしょうか。これはその人とタスクに依存します。

このインサイトでは、あなたの「落ち葉フロー」の結果を数百万人のメンバーと比較し、あなたのスピードと正確さのバランスを分析します。次回このゲームをプレイするとき、スピードと正確さを切り替え、あなたにとってベストのバランスを見つけましょう。"

"fit_test_edu_memory_matrix_description" : ""Kacheln Knobeln" fordert Sie dazu heraus, Ihren "visuell-räumlichen Notizblock" zu verwenden — ein Konzept des Arbeitsgedächtnisses des Psychologen Alan Baddeley.

Dieses wichtige kognitive Tool wird mit mehreren Teilen des Gehirns in Verbindung gebracht und speichert visuelle Informationen, wie Farben oder Formen und räumliche Informationen wie Lage und Position."
"fit_test_edu_memory_matrix_title" : "Kacheln Knobeln forderte Ihr räumliches Vorstellungsvermögen heraus."

"fit_test_edu_speed_match_description" : ""Kartenvergleich" fordert eine Form der Informationsverarbeitung heraus, die visuelle Verarbeitung genannt wird. Um schnelle Entscheidungen treffen zu können, muss Ihr Gehirn die auf den Karten abgebildeten Symbole schnell verarbeiten.

Dieser scheinbar einfache Prozess beansprucht viele Teile Ihres Gehirns, wie u.a. Ihren visuellen Cortex. Diese Neuronen, welches sich im hinteren Teil Ihres Gehirns befinden, verarbeiten Form, Farbe und Bewegungen — verwandeln Impulse in brauchbare Information."
"fit_test_edu_speed_match_title" : "Dieses Spiel fordert die Fähigkeit der Informationsverarbeitung heraus."

"fit_test_edu_train_of_thought_description" : "Bei der Aufmerksamkeit handelt es sich um eine eingeschränkte Ressource, die nur eine begrenzte Menge an Informationen auf einmal aufnehmen.

"insight_3_calculation_popup_body" : "Ihre Stärken und Schwächen basieren auf dem Lumosity Performance Index (LPI) für jedes Spiel. Der LPI ist eine standardisierte Skala, welche Vergleiche zwischen allen Spiele mit unterschiedlichen Scoring-Verfahren anstellt.

Diese Ergebnisse basieren auf Ihrem gegenwärtigen Spiele-LPI, welcher jedes Mal, wenn Sie ein Spiel spielen aktualisiert wird. Dies beinhaltet nur Spiele, die innerhalb der letzten sechs Monate gespielt wurden."

"insight_4_calculation_popup_body" : "Ihre Ergebnisse basieren auf dem Lumosity Performance Index (LPI) für jedes Spiel. Der LPI ist eine standardisierte Skala, welche Vergleiche über alle Spiele mit verschiedenen Scoringmethoden hinweg erlaubt.

Für jedes Spiel wird Ihr jüngster Spiele-LPI mit dem Spiele-LPI von vor 30 Tagen vergleichen. Dies beinhaltet nur Spiele, welche im letzten Monat gespielt wurden."
"insights_dialog_speed_accuracy_nodata_body" : "Wir erstellen immer noch Ihren Bericht. Kommen Sie morgen wieder!"

"insights_dialog_unlock_body" : "Jedes von Ihnen in der Trainingseinheit oder von der Spiele-Seite gespielte Spiel zählt zur Freischaltung Ihrer Einblicke.

Spielen Sie viele verschiedene Spiele, um eine bessere Qualität der Einblicke zu erhalten."

"insights_ebbflow_info_text" : "Zuerst fassten wir die von der Lumosity Community gespielten Spiele von "Fluss oder Richtung" zusammen und gruppierten sie nach Gesamtergebnissen. Dann berechneten wir die Geschwindigkeit sowie die Genauigkeit innerhalb einer jeden "Punkte-Gruppe". Basierend auf Ihrem letzten "Fluss oder Richtung"-Ergebnis vergleichen wir Ihre Geschwindigkeit und Genauigkeit mit den Ergebnissen Ihrer Gruppe.

Wenn Ihr Geschwindigkeits-Prozentrang in Ihrer Gruppe höher ist als Ihr Genauigkeits-Prozentrang, so wird der Schieber näher an "Geschwindigkeit" sein. Wenn Ihr Genauigkeit-Prozentrang höher ist, so wird der Schieber näher an "Genauigkeit" sein."

"insights_ebbflow_science" : "Wenn Sie eine Aufgabe Sie dazu herausfordert schnell und genau zu sein, so sehen Sie sich mit einem "Geschwindigkeit-Genauigkeit"-Kompromiss konfrontiert. Wenn Sie so schnell wie möglich vorgehen, riskieren Sie falsche Antworten und umgekehrt.

Für die EInblicke bei dem Spiel "Fluss oder Richtung" vergleichen wir Ihr Spiel mit dem Spiel von Millionen von anderen Nutzern, analysieren wir wie Sie bei diesem Spiel eine Balance zwischen Geschwindigkeit und Genauigkeit finden. Versuchen Sie das nächste Mal, ob Sie zwischen den Aufgaben Geschwindigkeit und Genauigkeit wechseln können und finden Sie die für Sie am besten funktionierende Balance."

"insights_lim_info_text" : "Jedes Mal, wenn Sie korrekt antworten, messen wir die Zeit, die Sie für Ihre Antwort benötigen. Anschließend berechnen wir zwei mittlere Reaktionszeiten; eine für die passenden Schwärme, die andere für nicht-passende Schwärme. "lim_compare_adaptive" : "Verglichen mit anderen Spielern Ihrer Altersgruppe, sind Sie adaptiv. Adaptive Spieler werden bei nicht-passenden Schwärmen langsamer, da Sie das Tempo der Genauigkeit anpassen. Denken Sie daran, das Tempo beizubehalten, damit Sie mehr Punkte erzielen."

"fit_test_edu_speed_match_description" : "스피드 카드는 정보처리의 한 유형인 시각적 처리를 자극합니다. 귀하의 두뇌는 빠른 결정을 내리기 위해 플래시카드의 심벌들을 처리해야 합니다. 

겉으로 간단해보이는 이 과정은 귀하의 시각 피질 및 뇌의 많은 부분의 활동을 수반합니다. 뇌의 뒷 쪽에 위치한 뉴런들은 원자극을 유용한 정보로 바꾸며 모양, 색, 움직임을 처리합니다."

"insight_3_calculation_popup_body" : "회원님의 강점과 약점은 각 게임 Lumosity 수행능력지수(LPI)를 기반으로 합니다. LPI는 다른 채점 방법을 가진 게임들 간 비교를 허용하는 표준화된 척도입니다.

해당 결과는 회원님의 현재 게임 LPI에 근거하며 게임을 플레이할 때마다 업데이트됩니다. 단 최근 6개월 이내 한 게임만 포함됩니다."

"insight_4_calculation_popup_body" : "회원님의 결과는 각 게임 Lumosity 수행능력지수(LPI)를 기반으로 합니다. LPI는 다른 채점 방법을 가진 게임들 간 비교를 허용하는 표준화된 척도입니다.

각 게임에서 회원님의 가장 최근 게임 LPI는 30일 이전의 게임 LPI와 비교됩니다. 단 최근 한 달 이내 최소 한 번 이상 플레이한 게임들만 포함됩니다."

더 나은 인사이트를 원한다면 다양한 게임을 목표로 해보세요."

"insights_ebbflow_info_text" : "우선 저희는 Lumosity 커뮤니티의 나뭇잎 행진 플레이에 대한 통계를 작성한 다음 이를 점수별로 그룹화했습니다. 그런 다음 각 "점수 그룹"의 평균 속도와 정확성을 산출했습니다. 여러분의 가장 최근 나뭇잎 행진 점수를 기준으로 저희는 여러분의 속도와 정확성을 여러분이 속한 그룹과 비교합니다. 

만약 여러분의 속도 백분율이 정확성 백분율보다 높다면 여러분의 위치는 "속도" 쪽에 보다 가까워 집니다. 정확성 백분율이 더 높다면 여러분의 위치는 "정확성" 쪽으로 기울 것입니다."

"insights_ebbflow_science" : "빠르고 정확하게 수행해야 하는 작업이 있을 때, 여러분은 "속도-정확성 교환"이라는 상황에 직면하게 됩니다. 최대한 빨리 수행한다면 정확성이 떨어지기 쉬우며, 그 반대도 마찬가지입니다. 그렇다면 어떤 것이 더 중요할까요? 그것은 개인과 작업별로 다릅니다. 

이러한 인사이트를 통해 저희는 여러분의 나뭇잎 행진 플레이를 수많은 다른 회원들의 플레이와 비교하고 플레이 시 여러분이 속도와 정확성의 균형을 어떻게 조절하는지 분석합니다. 그 다음에는 여러분이 그 두 가지를 서로 전환할 수 있는지 봅니다. 여러분에게 가장 적합한 균형을 찾아보세요!"

"fit_test_edu_memory_matrix_description" : "Cache-cache mémoire vous mets au défi d'utiliser votre calepin visuo-spatial, un concept de mémoire de travail développé par Alan Baddeley.

Associé à plusieurs parties de votre cerveau, cet outil cognitif important permet d'enregistrer des informations visuelles comme les couleurs ou les formes, ainsi que des informations spatiales comme les lieux."
"fit_test_edu_memory_matrix_title" : "Cache-cache mémoire a mis à l'épreuve votre rappel spatial."

"fit_test_edu_speed_match_description" : "À toute vitesse met à l'épreuve un type de traitement de l'information appelé le traitement visuel. Votre cerveau doit traiter les symboles affichés sur les cartes et prendre une décision rapidement.

Ce processus en apparence simple implique plusieurs parties de votre cerveau, tel que le cortex visuel. Ces neurones situés à l'arrière de votre cerveau, traitent les formes, couleurs ainsi que les mouvements, transformant les stimuli bruts en des informations utiles."
"fit_test_edu_speed_match_title" : "Ce jeu a mis à l'épreuve votre capacité à traiter les informations."

"fit_test_edu_train_of_thought_description" : "L'attention est une ressource limitée ne pouvant suivre qu'une certaine quantité d'information à la fois. Plus il y a de trains requérant votre concentration, plus il devient difficile de diriger un seul train correctement. 

Afin de réussir dans ce jeu, il vous faut constamment équilibrer deux procédés : se concentrer sur les informations nécessaires tout en ignorant celles inutiles."

"insight_3_calculation_popup_body" : "Vos forces et vos faiblesses sont basés sur l'Indice de Performance Lumosity (IPL) pour chaque jeu. IPL est l'échelle normale qui permet la comparaison entre les jeux avec différents méthodes de points.

Ces résultats sont basés sur votre LPI du jeu actuelle, qui est mis à jours chaque fois que vous jouez au jeu. Seulement les jeux joués au cours des derniers six mois sont inclus."

"insight_4_calculation_popup_body" : "Vos résultats sont basés dans l'évolution de l'Indice de Performance Lumosity (IPL) pour chaque jeu. L'IPL est l'échelle normale qui permet la comparaison entre les jeux avec différent méthodes de points. Pour chaque jeu, votre IPL a été comparé à votre IPL de jeu il y a 30 jours. Seul les jeux joués au moins une fois au cours du mois dernier sont inclus."

"insights_ebbflow_analyze_time" : "Analyse réalisée à partir du dernier jeu joué"

"insights_ebbflow_info_text" : "Tout d'abord, nous avons compilé les données de fluctuation de la communauté Lumosity et les avons regroupées par score. Ensuite, nous avons calculé la vitesse et précision moyennes pour chaque « groupe de score ». En nous basant sur votre dernier score de fluctuation, nous comparons vos vitesse et précision avec celles de votre groupe.

Si le centile de votre vitesse est plus élevé que celui de votre précision, votre repère sera plus près du côté « Vitesse » de la balance. Si le centile de votre précision est plus élevé, votre repère sera davantage du côté « Précision »."

"insights_ebbflow_science" : "Quand vous effectuez une tâche qui nécessite rapidité et précision, vous faites face à un « compromis vitesse-précision ». Si vous allez aussi vite que possible, vous avez tendance à sacrifier la précision, et vice versa. Lequel de ces critères est le plus important ? Cela dépend de la personne et de la tâche.

Pour cette analyse, nous comparons les fluctuations dans vos jeux à celles de millions d'autres joueurs, et analysons la manière dont la vitesse et la précision s'équilibrent. La prochaine fois, voyez si vous pouvez changer d'équilibre ! Trouvez celui qui vous convient !"
"insights_journey_get_the_most" : "Tirez le meilleur parti de votre entraînement"

"insights_lim_info_text" : "Chaque fois que vous répondez correctement, nous mesurons le temps que vous prenez pour répondre. Nous calculons alors deux temps de réponse médians : un pour les volées semblables, un autre pour les volés dissemblables. Nous utilisons ensuite ces calculs pour déterminer votre vitesse, exprimée en nombre de réponses correctes par minute."

"fit_test_edu_memory_matrix_description" : "Matriz de memoria pone a prueba el uso de tu agenda visoespacial, un concepto del modelo de memoria de trabajo propuesto por el psicólogo Alan Baddeley.

"fit_test_edu_speed_match_description" : "Veloz-mente pone a prueba un tipo de procesamiento de la información llamado procesamiento visual. Tu cerebro debe procesar los símbolos en las tarjetas para tomar decisiones rápidas.

Este proceso, aparentemente simple, involucra muchas partes de tu cerebro, como la corteza visual. Estas neuronas, situadas en la parte trasera del cerebro, procesan formas, colores y movimientos, transformando los estímulos en información útil."

"fit_test_edu_train_of_thought_description" : "La atención solo puede abarcar una cantidad limitada de información al mismo tiempo. Cuantos más trenes tengas que atender, más difícil te resultará dirigir cada tren correctamente.

"insight_3_calculation_popup_body" : "Tus puntos fuertes y débiles están basados en el Índice de desempeño de Lumosity (LPI) para cada juego. El LPI es una escala estandarizada que nos permite comparar resultados entre juegos con diferentes métodos de puntuación.

Estos resultados están basados en tu LPI de juego actual, que se actualizará cada vez que juegues a ese juego. Solo contabilizamos juegos jugados en las últimos seis meses."

"insight_4_calculation_popup_body" : "Tus resultados están basados en cambios en tu Índice de desempeño de Lumosity (LPI) para cada juego. El LPI es una escala estandarizada que nos permite comparar resultados entre juegos con diferentes métodos de puntuación.

Tu LPI más reciente en cada juego es comparado con el LPI de hace 30 días en el mismo juego .
Solo incluimos juegos jugados al menos una vez en el último mes."
"insights_dialog_speed_accuracy_nodata_body" : "Todavía estamos procesando tu informe. Vuelve mañana."

"insights_dialog_unlock_body" : "Cada partida que juegues en tus sesiones o desde la página de juegos te acercará más a desbloquear tus Análisis.

Para obtener análisis de mayor calidad, intenta jugar a diferentes juegos."

"insights_ebbflow_info_text" : "Primero, recopilamos las partidas de Hojas navegantes de la comunidad de Lumosity y las agrupamos por puntuación. Luego calculamos la velocidad y la precisión medias de cada "grupo de puntuación". Entonces, según tu puntuación más reciente en Hojas navegantes, comparamos tu velocidad y precisión con la de ese grupo.

Si tu percentil de velocidad es superior que tu percentil de precisión, tu resultado se acercará más al lado de la velocidad en la escala. Si tu percentil de precisión es más alto, tu resultado estará más cerca del lado de la precisión en la escala."

"insights_ebbflow_science" : "Cuando realizas una actividad que requiere velocidad y precisión, te enfrentas ante una disyuntiva entre estas dos destrezas. Al aumentar la velocidad, sacrificas precisión y viceversa. Pero, ¿qué es más importante? Depende de la persona y de la actividad.

En este análisis comparamos tus partidas de Hojas navegantes con millones de partidas de otros jugadores y analizamos cómo equilibras la velocidad y la precisión cuando juegas. La próxima vez que juegues, prueba a centrarte más en una u otra destreza y encuentra el equilibrio que mejor te funcione."

"insights_lim_info_text" : "Cada vez que respondas correctamente, medimos el tiempo que tardas. Luego calculamos la media de dos tiempos de respuesta: una para las bandadas que coinciden y otra para las que no coinciden. A partir de ambas medias definimos tu velocidad, que se expresa en número de respuestas correctas por minuto."

"lim_compare_1" : "Eres más sensible con las bandadas que no coinciden que la mayoría de personas de tu edad."
"lim_compare_2" : "Eres igual de sensible con las bandadas que no coinciden que la mayoría de personas de tu edad."
"lim_compare_3" : "Eres menos sensible con las bandadas que no coinciden que la mayoría de personas de tu edad."

"lim_compare_adaptive" : "En comparación con la mayoría de personas de tu edad, usas una estrategia adaptativa. Los jugadores adaptativos se ralentizan con las bandadas que no coinciden para ajustar su precisión. Cuando juegues, intenta mantener el ritmo para obtener una mayor puntuación."

"lim_compare_balanced" : "En comparación con la mayoría de personas de tu edad, usas una estrategia equilibrada. Los jugadores equilibrados se ralentizan un poco con las bandadas que no coinciden para mejorar su precisión, pero en general mantienen bien el ritmo. Cuando juegues, prueba a mejorar la velocidad o a centrarte más en la precisión."

"lim_compare_consistent" : "En comparación con la mayoría de personas de tu edad, usas una estrategia lineal. Los jugadores lineales no se ralentizan con las bandadas que no coinciden, a pesar del riesgo de cometer algunos fallos, y en general responden a más bandadas. Cuando juegues, intenta mantener la precisión con las bandadas."

"lim_report_description" : "En Perdido en el vuelo, la gente suele responder más despacio a las bandadas que no coinciden: esto es, cuando los pájaros van en direcciones distintas.

La razón es que la atención selectiva de nuestro cerebro debe centrarse a la vez en el pájaro del medio y descartar el resto de la bandada."

"fit_test_edu_memory_matrix_description" : "Matriz de Memória desafia você a usar o seu "bloco de esboço visuoespacial", conceito criado a partir do modelo de memória operacional do psicólogo Alan Baddeley.

Associada a várias partes do seu cérebro, essa ferramenta cognitiva importante armazena informações visuais como cor ou forma, além de informações espaciais como localização."
"fit_test_edu_memory_matrix_title" : "Matriz de Memória desafiou a sua memória espacial."

"fit_test_edu_speed_match_description" : "Correspondência rápida desafia um tipo de processamento de informações chamado de processamento visual. O seu cérebro deve processar os símbolos nas cartas apresentadas para tomar uma decisão rápida.

Este processo aparentemente simples envolve muitas partes do seu cérebro, como o seu córtex visual. Esses neurônios, localizados na parte de trás do seu cérebro, processam formas, cores e movimentos — transformando estímulos brutos em informações úteis."
"fit_test_edu_speed_match_title" : "Este jogo desafiou as suas habilidades em processamento de informações."

"fit_test_edu_train_of_thought_description" : "Atenção é um recurso limitado que pode acompanhar apenas uma certa quantidade de informação, de uma só vez. Quanto maior o número de trens nos quais você foca a sua atenção, mais difícil é guiar cada trem corretamente.

Para ter um bom desempenho neste jogo, você deve balancear dois processos, constantemente: concentrar-se nas informações necessárias e ignorar as que são dispensáveis."

"insight_3_calculation_popup_body" : "eus pontos fracos e fortes são baseados no Índice de Performance Lumosity (IPL) de cada jogo. O IPL é uma escala padronizada que permite comparações entre jogos com diferentes métodos de pontuação.

Esses resultados são baseados em seu IPL de jogo atual, que é atualizado cada vez que você joga o jogo.
Apenas jogos jogados nos últimos seis meses são incluídos."

"insight_4_calculation_popup_body" : "Seus resultados são baseados em mudanças no Índice de Performance Lumosity (IPL) de cada jogo. O IPL é uma escala padronizada que permite comparações entre jogos com diferentes métodos de pontuação.

Para cada jogo, o seu IPL de jogo mais recente foi comparado ao seu IPL de jogo de 30 dias atrás.
Apenas jogos jogados ao menos uma vez no último mês são incluídos."

"insights_dialog_unlock_body" : "Todos os jogos de suas sessões de treino ou de sua página de Jogos contam para o desbloqueio de suas Descobertas.

Para Descobertas de maior qualidade, tente uma variedade mais ampla de jogos."

"insights_ebbflow_info_text" : "Primeiro, compilamos a forma da comunidade Lumosity jogar Folhas navegantes e agrupamos por pontuação. Depois, calculamos a velocidade e precisão média de cada "grupo de pontuação". Baseado em sua pontuação em Folhas navegantes, comparamos sua rapidez e precisão com seu grupo.

Se seu percentil de velocidade for maior que seu percentil de precisão, seu marcador estará mais próximo do lado "Velocidade" da escala. Se seu percentil de precisão for mais alto, seu marcador tenderá para o lado "Precisão"."

"insights_ebbflow_science" : "Ao fazer uma tarefa que exige rapidez e precisão, você encara uma escolha entre velocidade e precisão. Se você for o mais rápido possível, tende a sacrificar a precisão e vice-versa. Mas qual deles é o mais importante? Depende da pessoa e da tarefa.

Nesta Descoberta, comparamos sua forma de jogar Folhas navegantes com milhões de outros e analisamos como você equilibra rapidez e precisão ao jogar. Da próxima vez, tente trocar seu estilo. Encontre o equilíbrio que funciona melhor para você!"

"insights_lim_info_text" : "Sempre que você responde corretamente, nós medimos o tempo que você leva para responder. Então, calculamos dois tempos médios de resposta: um para os bandos que combinam e outro para os bandos que não combinam. Usamos essas médias para determinar sua velocidade, expressa pelo número de respostas corretas por minuto."

playstore_details.title: Lumosity: Brain Training
playstore_details.description:
Lumosity’s cognitive training program is a fun, interactive way to train your brain and learn about how your mind works. Used by over 100 million people worldwide, Lumosity’s program consists of science-based games designed to exercise memory, attention, speed, flexibility and problem-solving. 

Begin with a free 10-minute Fit Test to set your baseline scores and see how you compare with others your age. 

THE APP INCLUDES
•50+ activities ...and counting. 
•Challenges for memory, speed, logic, problem-solving, math, language, and more. 
•Regularly release of new features.

WORKOUT MODES
•Carefully curated sets of games made for you. 
•Personalized tracking of training habits and preferences to find different ways to challenge your brain.

DETAILED TRAINING INSIGHTS
•Learn your game strengths, weaknesses and cognitive patterns.
•Analysis of your game play to make connections to daily life.

THE STORY BEHIND LUMOSITY®
We’re a team of scientists and designers exploring new ways to challenge the brain and push cognitive research forward. We take common cognitive and neuropsychological tasks, or create entirely new, experimental challenges. Working with experienced designers, we transform these tasks into games and puzzles that challenge core cognitive skills.

We also work with 40+ university researchers worldwide. We give qualified researchers free access to Lumosity training and tools, helping them investigate new areas in cognition.

We invite you to train with us and join in our mission to advance the understanding of human cognition.

The app is available in English, Spanish, Portuguese, French, German, Japanese and Korean. To access the app in one of these languages, change your device setting to the desired language.

GET HELP: http://www.lumosity.com/help
FOLLOW US: http://twitter.com/lumosity
LIKE US: http://facebook.com/lumosity

LUMOSITY PREMIUM PRICING & TERMS
With Lumosity Premium, you will work out with a personalized training program, unlock in-depth insights about how you play, and receive tips for better game accuracy, speed and strategy. We offer the following Premium subscriptions:
Monthly: $11.99 USD/month
Yearly: $59.99 USD/year

These prices are for United States customers. Pricing in other countries may vary, and actual charges may be converted to your local currency depending on your country of residence.

Lumosity Premium subscriptions are charged through your Google Play account upon confirmation of purchase. Your subscription will automatically renew at the price and period selected above unless you turn off auto-renewal at least 24 hours before the end of the current period. You will be charged for renewal within 24 hours prior to the end of the current period. You may manage your subscription and turn off auto-renewal in your Google Play account settings after purchase. Refunds are not provided for the unused portion of any term, and any unused portion of a free trial period will be forfeited when a purchase is made.

Privacy Policy:
https://www.lumosity.com/legal/privacy_policy
Terms of Service:
https://www.lumosity.com/legal/terms_of_service
Payment Policy:
https://www.lumosity.com/legal/payment_policy
